.TH "legacy_suspend" 9 "legacy_suspend" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
legacy_suspend \- Execute a legacy (bus or class) suspend callback for device.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" legacy_suspend
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "pm_message_t state "  ","
.BI "int (*cb)(struct device *dev, pm_message_t state) "  ","
.BI "const char *info "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
Device to suspend.
.IP "state" 12
PM transition of the system being carried out.
.IP "cb" 12
Suspend callback to execute.
.IP "info" 12
string description of caller.
